Aim :
To implement various string operations.

Algorithm:
Step 1: Start the program.

Step 2: Read the first string a from the user.

Step 3: Read the second string b from the user.

Step 4: Convert the first string a to uppercase and display the result.

Step 5: Convert the first string a to lowercase and display the result.

Step 6: Convert the first string a to title case and display the result.

Step 7: Swap the case of characters in the first string a and display the result.

Step 8: Capitalize the first letter of the first string a and display the result.

Step 9: Perform the same string operations (upper, lower, title, swapcase, capitalize) on the second string b and display the results.

Step 10: Display the first five characters of the first string a using slicing.

Step 11: Display the first five characters of the second string b using slicing.

Step 12: Split both strings a and b into lists of words and display them.

Step 13: Find the position of the character 'h' in both strings using the find() function and display the result.

Step 14: Replace the character 'a' with 'b' in both strings and display the modified strings.

Step 15: Calculate and display the length of both strings.

Step 16: Stop the program.
